verses.verse: O come, <WH3212> let us sing <WH7442> to the LORD: <WH3068> let us make a joyful noise to the rock <WH6697> of our salvation. <WH3468>
Let us come <WH6923> before <WH6924> his presence <WH6440> with thanksgiving, <WH8426> and make a joyful noise to him with psalms. <WH2158>
For the LORD <WH3068> is a great <WH1419> God, <WH410> and a great <WH1419> King <WH4428> above <WH5921> all <WH3605> gods. <WH430>
In his hand <WH3027> are the deep <WH4278> places of the earth: <WH776> the strength <WH8443> of the hills <WH2022> is his also.
The sea <WH3220> is his, and he made <WH6213> it: and his hands <WH3027> formed <WH3335> the dry <WH3006> land.
O come, <WH935> let us worship <WH7812> and bow <WH3766> down: <WH3766> let us kneel <WH1288> before <WH6440> the LORD <WH3068> our maker. <WH6213>
For he is our God; <WH430> and we are the people <WH5971> of his pasture, <WH4830> and the sheep <WH6629> of his hand. <WH3027> To day <WH3117> if <WH518> you will hear <WH8085> his voice, <WH6963>
Harden <WH7185> not your heart, <WH3824> as in the provocation, <WH4808> and as in the day <WH3117> of temptation <WH4531> in the wilderness: <WH4057>
When <WH834> your fathers <WH1> tempted <WH5254> me, proved <WH974> me, and saw <WH7200> my work. <WH6467>

Forty <WH705> years <WH8141> long was I grieved <WH6962> with this generation, <WH1755> and said, <WH559> It is a people <WH5971> that do err <WH8582> in their heart, <WH3824> and they have not known <WH3045> my ways: <WH1870>
To whom <WH834> I swore <WH7650> in my wrath <WH639> that they should not enter <WH935> into <WH413> my rest. <WH4496>
